   Annuity Rate Verification Letter

   Rate verification letters can only be provided to individuals who have
   retired and are receiving benefits from the RRB. If you have not
   retired but would like to receive an estimate of your annuity, please
   contact your local field office.

   Request an Annuity Rate Verification Letter  Now
   If you want to request a letter verifying your annuity rate now, simply
   click the button below and we will take you to the online request form.

   Additional information on the currently available services are
   described by selecting the buttons to the left or at the bottom of this
   page.  These areas can also be accessed for assistance in understanding
   the services that are mailed to you.

   About Your Annuity Rate Verification Letter

   Your Annuity Rate Verification Letter is a short letter detailing your
   current annuity rate. The letter lists the effective date of your total
   monthly rate and any Medicare deductions. Your letter will be mailed to
   the address we have on record.


